article.headline: Radford 63, VMI 46
article.story: RADFORD, Va. (AP) -- Chris Goodin scored 18 points, including four 3-pointers, and Whit Holcomb-Faye added 17 as Radford beat VMI 63-46 in a Big South Conference game on Wednesday night. The Highlanders (10-10, 6-4) shot 8-of-16 on 3-pointers and also suffocated VMI (5-15, 3-7) on defense, outscoring the Keydets 20-9 off turnovers. Radford held VMI to 39 percent shooting on the game. Radee Skipworth paced the Keydets with 13 points and six rebounds. Radford led 35-21 at the break.
